sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Assembled using parts from the 2011 iGEM distribution.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PCB chromophore module with J23113 low expression promoter and B1001 terminator. *Heme oxygenase and phycocyanobilin:ferredoxin oxidoreductase *Used for light sensing system *Low expression with J23113 promoter *B1001 terminator instead of B0015, lambda-red compatible
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Due to the toxic nature of HO1 and pcyA enzymatic activities, we added a very weak promoter (J23113) to the PCB chromophore module.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Assembled using parts from the MIT 2011 iGEM distribution.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is the PCB chromophore module without promoter, with B1001 terminator.
*Heme oxygenase and phycocyanobilin:ferredoxin oxidoreductase *Used for light sensing system *Recommend weak promoters *B1001 terminator instead of B0015, lambda-red compatible
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
B1001 instead of B0015 since this part was chosen to put into the bacterial chromosome using lambda-red recombination. The standard double terminator B0015 has extensive homologous sites within E.coli genome, therefore it's not used.
This part lacks promoter. What promoter to be used is up to the user. However, we recommend weak promoters due to HO1's enzymatic activity kills cells by consuming heme.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
